. Homology modeling suggests an additional helix &#x3B1;4 (disordered residues <span class="ins cts-1" title="Rule: hyphens to endash(&#x2013;) between number ranges; : 609" data-cid="10072" data-userid="1" data-username="Exeter" data-time="1451642784000" data-type="ruleset">
79&#x2013;92</span>
<span class="del cts-1" title="Rule: hyphens to endash(&#x2013;) between number ranges; : 609" data-cid="10073" data-userid="1" data-username="Exeter" data-time="1451642784000" data-type="ruleset">
79-92</span>
) forming an arch with helix &#x3B1;6. The protein is shown in a simplified surface representation with the same colors as in <span class="jrnlFigRef" data-citation-string=" F1 ">
